<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911203-0024</DOCNO><DOCID>911203-0024.</DOCID><HL>   Unisys Stock Price Jumps   On Takeover Speculation</HL><DATE>12/03/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A3</SO><CO>   BAB U.CPT UIS</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)FINANCIAL (FIN)TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>AIRLINES (AIR)ALL BANKS, BANKING NEWS AND ISSUES (BNK)COMPUTERS AND INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY (CPR)SECURITIES (SCR)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>EUROPE (EU)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PENNSYLVANIA (PA)GREAT BRITAIN (UK)UNITED STATES (US)WESTERN EUROPE (WEU)</RE><LP>   NEW YORK -- Stock of Unisys Corp. soared by 37% on areport that an investor group is working on a takeover bid.   Shares of the Blue Bell, Pa., computer concern were quotedat $5.125, up $1.375, on volume of about nine million shares,making it the most actively traded stock on the New YorkStock Exchange.</LP><TEXT>   The report in USA Today said the investors are working ona takeover plan with Charterhouse Bank Ltd., a Londonmerchant bank. The story said the group's members may includeLord King, chairman of British Airways PLC, a formerexecutive of International Business Machines Corp., and aprofessor at Massachusetts Institute of Technology. Thereport said the group had $500 million in committed equityfinancing.   Officials at Charterhouse didn't return calls. A spokesmanfor British Airways said he didn't have any response to thereport. And the MIT professor, Kenneth Smith, didn't returncalls. A spokesman for Unisys declined to comment on thereport.   Some Wall Street analysts were skeptical about prospectsfor any bid. Unisys had $3.43 billion in debt at the end ofthe third quarter and about $1.5 billion of preferred stock.Its common stock alone has a value of about $820 million atthe current market price. The company has reported hugelosses for 1990, and just withdrew a planned $440 millionoffering of stock in its defense electronics business.</TEXT></DOC>